726074f-b.text:
34-11 to 34-19 Astoria Boulevard, north side, between 34th and 35th Streets. The frame house is no. 34-11 and 15. These, as well as other buildings on the north side of the Boulevard, were later torn down for the construction of the Grand Central Parkway approach
to the Triborouush Bridge.
View 2 shows the smae group of buildings being torn down, seen
from 35th Street.
View 1: March 11, 1931
View 2: September 20, 1934
P. L. Snerr
